President Trump visited Afghanistan on Thanksgiving Day and had a meeting with the President of Afghanistan, Ashraf Ghani. During the visit, President Trump stated that the US has had tremendous success in the fight against ISIS, with the group being severely hit and down to a very small number. He also mentioned that the Taliban wants to make a deal, and the US is in talks with them. President Trump emphasized the importance of a ceasefire in any potential deal. He also discussed the US presence in Syria and the success in fighting ISIS there. President Ghani thanked President Trump for his leadership and support, and highlighted the progress made by Afghan security forces. The two leaders discussed the number of troops in Afghanistan, but specific numbers were not provided. President Trump expressed the desire for other countries in the region to contribute to the fight against terrorism.